Package: claudeqt
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         claudeqt-common (= ${source:Version})
Recommends: claudeqt-remote
Description: Native Qt6 GUI for Claude Code CLI
 ClaudeQt provides a native desktop interface around the Claude Code
 command-line tool, supporting session management, projects, MCP,
 slash commands, and remote daemon connections.
 .
 Requires Claude Code CLI to be installed separately. Anthropic does not
 ship a Debian package; install via the upstream native installer
 (curl -fsSL https://claude.ai/install.sh | bash) or npm
 (@anthropic-ai/claude-code). ClaudeQt detects the CLI at startup and
 offers a first-run dialog with installation instructions if not found.

Package: claudeqt-remote
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         claudeqt-common (= ${source:Version}),
         adduser,
         systemd,
         openssl
Description: Headless ClaudeQt remote daemon
 Runs Claude Code CLI on a host and exposes it over JSON-RPC/TLS to a
 remote ClaudeQt GUI. Ships with a systemd unit that uses IPAddressAllow
 for pre-accept IP filtering and defaults to localhost-only until an
 admin drops in an allowlist extension.
 .
 Creates a dedicated system user 'claudeqt' (shell /usr/sbin/nologin,
 home /var/lib/claudeqt). After installing this package, follow the
 NEXT STEPS hint printed by postinst to install Claude Code CLI under
 the daemon identity; authentication can be done locally via 'claude
 /login' OR deferred to connect time (the ClaudeQt GUI can forward your
 desktop login over the encrypted channel — see README.Debian for both
 paths). The daemon then picks up the binary at
 /var/lib/claudeqt/.local/bin/claude automatically.

Package: claudeqt-common
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         python3 (>= 3.12),
         python3-anyio
Description: Shared data files for ClaudeQt
 Icons, desktop entry, default CLAUDE.md templates, translations, and the
 Python engine bridge package (claudeqt_engine) used by both claudeqt
 and claudeqt-remote.
